- Is there a draft? I'll close it.
- No, Father.

14
00:01:31,329 --> 00:01:33,417
Are you with one of these two?

15
00:01:34,423 --> 00:01:35,868
No.

16
00:01:37,177 --> 00:01:39,174
Okay, turn around.

17
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:44,393
If you see me again and I'm not smiling,
I don't think you're going to like it.

18
00:01:44,830 --> 00:01:47,055
Now get back in there.

19
00:01:52,814 --> 00:01:56,977
- Are you leaving?
- Just to get some air.

20
00:01:57,374 --> 00:01:59,481
You don't have to be polite.

21
00:01:59,516 --> 00:02:02,651
I'm sorry. I didn't want
to lie to you in here.

22
00:02:02,686 --> 00:02:05,264
- I'm Father Gill.
- I'm Peggy Olsen.

23
00:02:05,299 --> 00:02:07,404
- Oh, Katherine Olsen's girl.
- Yes.

24
00:02:07,439 --> 00:02:09,806
I'm having dinner at your sister's.

25
00:02:09,841 --> 00:02:13,017
- Are you a new priest?
- I'm visiting.

26
00:02:15,995 --> 00:02:18,667
So are you going to come back in?

27
00:02:18,692 --> 00:02:20,111
Yes.

28
00:02:35,471 --> 00:02:37,143
Hello.

29
00:02:38,258 --> 00:02:40,713
Good morning, Caroline.

30
00:02:41,788 --> 00:02:45,042
Yes. We're up.

31
00:02:45,994 --> 00:02:47,991
Barbecue.

32
00:02:48,588 --> 00:02:53,414
Right. Caroline, we
went over this. Steaks.

33
00:02:53,449 --> 00:02:56,263
And the kids can eat hot dogs.

34
00:02:56,298 --> 00:02:57,933
Cancel.

35
00:02:57,968 --> 00:03:00,849
I'm sorry. What?

36
00:03:01,861 --> 00:03:05,140
I don't know. Jell-O?

37
00:03:05,175 --> 00:03:07,672
Do you want me to
pick something else up?

38
00:03:07,674 --> 00:03:09,007
Cancel.

39
00:03:10,462 --> 00:03:14,810
Caroline, hold on a sec. I can't.

40
00:03:19,655 --> 00:03:25,574
Caroline, I feel terrible about
this, but Don's not feeling well.

41
00:03:26,535 --> 00:03:29,571
No. I'm sorry.

42
00:03:30,945 --> 00:03:35,328
The 22nd?
Isn't that Easter?

43
00:03:35,363 --> 00:03:39,036
Good. Bye-bye.

44
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,727
What's with you?

45
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,656
I don't know.

46
00:03:44,983 --> 00:03:47,768
I had an amazing dream.

47
00:03:57,575 --> 00:03:59,731
- You're always hogging the TV.
- I don't like baby stuff.

48
00:03:59,766 --> 00:04:02,854
Get out.
We're- sleeping.

49
00:04:02,889 --> 00:04:06,036
Get some Raisin Bran.
You can eat it in the den.

50
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:08,422
Out!

51
00:04:09,293 --> 00:04:11,469
Out!

52
00:04:15,397 --> 00:04:17,638
I should have locked the door.

53
00:04:36,973 --> 00:04:40,733
- Here's number 2, sir.
- Thank you, Jeeves.

54
00:04:41,582 --> 00:04:45,683
- Why are we in the living room?
- Because we live here.

55
00:04:49,858 --> 00:04:52,167
What did I say about the stereo?

56
00:04:52,202 --> 00:04:54,774
I wasn't touching it.

57
00:04:56,308 --> 00:04:59,384
- Bobby, I saw you do it.
- I didn't do it.

58
00:04:59,419 --> 00:05:01,716
Go watch TV, both of you.

59
00:05:09,265 --> 00:05:11,257
I love this song.

60
00:05:12,570 --> 00:05:14,587
His voice is like silk,

61
00:05:14,622 --> 00:05:17,411
and you can really hear the words.

62
00:05:18,168 --> 00:05:21,384
He makes everything
sound like Christmas.

63
00:05:22,102 --> 00:05:25,881
In high school I used to
love dancing to this song.

64
00:05:27,184 --> 00:05:29,032
Come dance with me.

65
00:05:30,478 --> 00:05:31,987
I thought we weren't
doing anything today.

66
00:05:32,022 --> 00:05:34,336
Hurry. It's almost over.

67
00:05:42,433 --> 00:05:45,520
I hate to think about your
reputation in high school.

68
00:05:58,057 --> 00:06:00,440
Are you going to sit at the table?

69
00:06:01,103 --> 00:06:03,972
- Gerry, could you get it?
- Jesus, Anita, I can't move.

70
00:06:04,007 --> 00:06:07,771
<i>Watch your language! And I don't care if
you have to lay there. Put your shoes on!</i>

71
00:06:07,806 --> 00:06:11,040
- Little Gerry, get my shoes!
- Do you want me to get the door?

72
00:06:11,075 --> 00:06:14,389
I can't reach my toes.
What am I supposed to do?

73
00:06:17,919 --> 00:06:19,843
Hello, Father.

74
00:06:19,878 --> 00:06:21,341
You're not leaving, are you?

75
00:06:21,376 --> 00:06:27,284
Hello, Father. I'm sorry I'm late.
I went by Green-Wood to visit my son.

76
00:06:27,619 --> 00:06:30,011
Well, I would love to meet him.

77
00:06:30,436 --> 00:06:32,092
It's a cemetery.

78
00:06:32,304 --> 00:06:36,418
Father, welcome.
Come before it gets cold.

79
00:06:37,607 --> 00:06:39,274
Hello, Father.

80
00:06:39,309 --> 00:06:41,093
I'm sorry I missed
Mass. My back is out.

81
00:06:41,128 --> 00:06:44,605
He hasn't been feeling well, but he
did his part. He watched the baby.

82
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:47,777
Well, I, uh, hope you feel better soon.

83
00:06:47,812 --> 00:06:51,323
- We all do.
- I'm sorry. I got to lay down.

84
00:06:51,642 --> 00:06:54,184
Oh, please, please.

85
00:06:54,715 --> 00:06:56,221
Oh, come.

86
00:06:56,256 --> 00:07:00,491
Of course, Father. Right
this way. We have you here.

87
00:07:00,526 --> 00:07:03,822
Gerard! Mikey! Wash your hands!

88
00:07:04,384 --> 00:07:06,690
They've disappeared.

89
00:07:06,725 --> 00:07:08,996
Uh, don't wait for them.

90
00:07:11,803 --> 00:07:14,511
Father, would you
honor us and say grace?

91
00:07:14,546 --> 00:07:16,697
Certainly. Why not?

92
00:07:17,816 --> 00:07:20,760
O Lord, thank You for
this wonderful feast.

93
00:07:20,795 --> 00:07:25,849
Thank you for these people
and this parish and their home.

94
00:07:28,928 --> 00:07:34,031
That was beautiful. Are
you doing to say grace now?

95
00:07:36,835 --> 00:07:40,727
Bless us, O Lord, and these Thy gifts
we are about to receive from Thy bounty,

96
00:07:40,762 --> 00:07:43,193
and make us ever mindful
of the needs of others.

97
00:07:43,228 --> 00:07:46,259
- Through Christ our Lord.
- Amen.

98
00:07:59,816 --> 00:08:02,884
Monsignor says you have
a beautiful singing voice.

99
00:08:02,919 --> 00:08:05,546
- And you play the harmonica?
- The guitar.

100
00:08:05,581 --> 00:08:08,722
I actually learned how to play
the mandolin when I was in Rome.

101
00:08:08,757 --> 00:08:11,668
- And soccer.
- Did you meet the Holy Father?

102
00:08:11,703 --> 00:08:13,155
Not exactly.

103
00:08:13,190 --> 00:08:17,377
It's kind of like being in Washington
and asking if you've met the President.

104
00:08:17,412 --> 00:08:20,180
But you know when he's in the building.

105
00:08:22,025 --> 00:08:24,511
- Well, aren't you going to have one?
- Should I?

106
00:08:24,546 --> 00:08:27,443
Well, I'm not going to drink by myself.

107
00:08:27,478 --> 00:08:30,341
- I'll get the sherry.
- I'll get it, Ma.

108
00:08:30,838 --> 00:08:32,840
I've always wanted to go to Rome.

109
00:08:32,875 --> 00:08:38,813
Ah, yes, well, Vatican City is one thing,
but then you realize you're in Italy.

110
00:08:38,848 --> 00:08:40,907
Peggy works in Manhattan.

111
00:08:40,942 --> 00:08:43,312
Oh, really? What do you do, Peggy?

112
00:08:43,347 --> 00:08:48,028
She works on Madison Avenue. She comes
up with the words in advertisements.

113
00:08:48,063 --> 00:08:49,956
They call it copywriting, Ma.

114
00:08:49,991 --> 00:08:53,441
Father, I'm glad you're here. I
didn't know they knew what I did.

115
00:08:53,476 --> 00:08:55,839
Oh, stop it. No, you
should see her work.

116
00:08:55,874 --> 00:08:59,123
Lipstick, reducing
programs, feminine products.

117
00:08:59,158 --> 00:09:00,803
Mom, not in front of Father.

118
00:09:00,838 --> 00:09:03,389
She used to do her
presentations for us.

119
00:09:03,424 --> 00:09:06,031
She uses Latin.

120
00:09:07,389 --> 00:09:09,993
I'm sorry to do this,
but I really should go.

121
00:09:10,028 --> 00:09:12,598
Oh. Look at that. Well,
where are you headed?

122
00:09:12,633 --> 00:09:14,504
I'll give you a lift. I have a car.

123
00:09:14,539 --> 00:09:16,627
To the 4th Avenue BMT?

124
00:09:17,672 --> 00:09:19,931
It is such an honor to
have you in our house.

125
00:09:19,966 --> 00:09:22,839
And I'm sorry the
chicken was overcooked.

126
00:09:22,874 --> 00:09:25,713
The chicken was perfect,
and you know that.

127
00:09:25,748 --> 00:09:27,288
Go get the Brownie.

128
00:09:27,323 --> 00:09:28,570
Let me wrap up some cake.

129
00:09:28,605 --> 00:09:31,407
Oh, thank you, but
no, thank you, Anita.

130
00:09:31,442 --> 00:09:34,103
You've all really made me homesick.

131
00:09:34,138 --> 00:09:37,097
Father, would you mind?

132
00:09:43,878 --> 00:09:47,364
- Say cheese.
- Cheese. Cheese.

133
00:09:55,240 --> 00:10:00,225
Brooks, have you made any decision
about our immediate future?

134
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:05,200
Believe it or not, Daddy, Brooks
has other interests besides drinking.

135
00:10:05,235 --> 00:10:06,754
That'll change.

136
00:10:06,789 --> 00:10:10,442
- Would you stop scaring them?
- We're not scared.

137
00:10:10,477 --> 00:10:12,164
Then how is it you've
been engaged for two months

138
00:10:12,199 --> 00:10:14,076
and you're not running
around making wedding plans?

139
00:10:14,111 --> 00:10:15,906
Because I told you.

140
00:10:15,941 --> 00:10:18,685
We don't like the idea
of having a big wedding.

141
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:21,841
- It doesn't have to be big.
- We think it's silly.

142
00:10:21,876 --> 00:10:24,987
You have to invite a bunch
of strangers to gawk at us

143
00:10:25,022 --> 00:10:28,061
to somehow prove our
feelings for each other.

144
00:10:28,842 --> 00:10:31,487
You know, it's embarrassing.

145
00:10:33,868 --> 00:10:36,012
Brooks?

146
00:10:36,658 --> 00:10:38,678
Whatever she wants.

147
00:10:39,724 --> 00:10:42,199
Well, your mother wants a wedding.

148
00:10:42,616 --> 00:10:45,349
- Mommy had a wedding.
- I did.

149
00:10:45,626 --> 00:10:50,943
Wearing that dress, my sister
and my mother fussing over me.

150
00:10:50,978 --> 00:10:54,932
It w the best I ever looked
in my life. The Pierre.

151
00:10:56,224 --> 00:10:59,843
I was drunk, and I didn't
have a glass of champagne.

152
00:10:59,878 --> 00:11:02,919
Gliding around in your father's arms.

153
00:11:02,954 --> 00:11:05,919
You know how good a dancer he is.

154
00:11:06,213 --> 00:11:10,256
Dancing with Grandpa.
I don't want you to miss that.

155
00:11:18,768 --> 00:11:20,772
What are you getting?

156
00:11:21,197 --> 00:11:24,643
I'll have the mussels
with garlic if you do.

157
00:11:25,169 --> 00:11:27,769
That's sweet.

158
00:11:34,696 --> 00:11:36,889
Thank you for the ride, Father.

159
00:11:37,097 --> 00:11:39,821
- Peggy, wait.
- Yes?

160
00:11:41,787 --> 00:11:46,174
I want to ask you about
something, and it's personal.

161
00:11:47,371 --> 00:11:49,215
Okay.

162
00:11:50,973 --> 00:11:54,721
I have the honor of delivering
the sermon next Sunday.

163
00:11:55,269 --> 00:11:59,409
It's Palm Sunday. That's a biggie.
I mean, you're on deck for Easter.

164
00:11:59,444 --> 00:12:04,325
And, well, uh, you said
you did presentations.

165
00:12:05,146 --> 00:12:07,874
Can I run some things past you?

166
00:12:10,593 --> 00:12:14,160
I don't know what I could tell you.
You must do this all the time.

167
00:12:14,195 --> 00:12:17,727
Well, I've done it, but your
monsignor is a tough act to follow.

168
00:12:20,094 --> 00:12:22,777
I don't know that I'm your audience.

169
00:12:22,812 --> 00:12:27,219
You were leaving, and we ended
up having supper together,

170
00:12:27,254 --> 00:12:30,764
and you're the only person in this
parish that knows about public speaking.

171
00:12:35,997 --> 00:12:38,958
I find that if I'm prepared

172
00:12:38,993 --> 00:12:43,907
and I have confidence in what I'm
selling, that kills the butterflies.

173
00:12:44,273 --> 00:12:49,526
That's good. I'm prepared.
Do you have any other tips?

174
00:12:50,613 --> 00:12:56,194
Well, pick somebody, and
make eye contact with them.

175
00:12:56,229 --> 00:13:00,436
You'd think it would make you
nervous, but it really focuses you.

176
00:13:03,929 --> 00:13:06,629
Don't they have stuff thatou're
supposed to talk about?

177
00:13:06,664 --> 00:13:08,751
Yes, they have stuff.

178
00:13:08,786 --> 00:13:12,860
Let's just say I'm covered
in the content department.

179
00:13:14,490 --> 00:13:16,599
I can only speak for myself,

180
00:13:16,634 --> 00:13:20,457
but the sermon is the only
part of Mass that's in English,

181
00:13:20,492 --> 00:13:23,508
and it's very hard to tell sometimes.

182
00:13:23,543 --> 00:13:26,152
Maybe be simpler?

183
00:13:26,621 --> 00:13:29,877
Give us a chance of understanding.

184
00:13:31,085 --> 00:13:34,813
Thank you for the ride. I should
go. I really do have to work.

185
00:13:34,848 --> 00:13:40,302
Idle hands. It's good to
know you. Have a great week.

186
00:14:05,028 --> 00:14:07,746
- I hate my feet.
- I love your feet, Mommy.

187
00:14:08,591 --> 00:14:11,871
Feet? I thought those were water skis.

188
00:14:12,324 --> 00:14:17,272
Stop it. Stop it! Stop it! Stop it!

189
00:14:20,054 --> 00:14:24,837
- Great. You broke it.
- I didn't mean to.

190
00:14:25,181 --> 00:14:28,065
You're being wild in
the house. It's late.

191
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:30,950
Everybody brush your
teeth and go to bed.

192
00:14:30,985 --> 00:14:34,145
- I'm hungry.
- You're going to bed.

193
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:37,501
We didn't have any dinner.

194
00:14:39,984 --> 00:14:42,325
It's 7:30.

195
00:14:42,994 --> 00:14:47,006
Okay. Come downstairs.
I'll make you some grilled cheese.

196
00:14:47,476 --> 00:14:50,691
- Go. Go. Go.
- Come on.

197
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:05,750
And my wife says, "Duck and cover. "

198
00:15:13,173 --> 00:15:15,029
Well, look at this.

199
00:15:15,589 --> 00:15:19,490
- Marty, meet Vicki.
- Hello, Marty.

200
00:15:20,007 --> 00:15:22,172
I've heard so much about you,

201
00:15:22,207 --> 00:15:25,086
but you didn't tell me
about his wonderful head.

202
00:15:25,121 --> 00:15:28,522
- What about it?
- Ooh, someone thinks a lot.

203
00:15:28,557 --> 00:15:30,854
Well, look at that.
It's love at first rub.

204
00:15:31,961 --> 00:15:34,359
My head has been known
to make wishes come true.

205
00:15:36,086 --> 00:15:37,427
Don't get up.

206
00:15:37,462 --> 00:15:39,724
This is Marty
Hasselbach, from Gorton's.

207
00:15:39,759 --> 00:15:41,203
Nice to meet you. Roger Sterling.

208
00:15:41,238 --> 00:15:42,778
We were due to meet tomorrow anyway.

209
00:15:42,813 --> 00:15:44,867
- Love that frozen scrod.
- Thank you.

210
00:15:44,902 --> 00:15:47,605
I'm Vicki, Marty's wife.

211
00:15:49,489 --> 00:15:51,480
Aren't you a lucky man?

212
00:15:51,599 --> 00:15:54,145
Yes. Yes, I am.

213
00:15:54,180 --> 00:15:57,001
We were just discussing the male head.

214
00:15:57,481 --> 00:15:58,829
Is that right?

215
00:15:58,864 --> 00:16:01,022
I like the Yul Brynner look.

216
00:16:01,057 --> 00:16:02,680
She does seem to.

217
00:16:02,715 --> 00:16:05,066
I keep threatening to
shave him one morning.

218
00:16:05,101 --> 00:16:07,980
Just hop in the shower
and take it all off.

219
00:16:08,015 --> 00:16:09,431
Is that right?

220
00:16:09,466 --> 00:16:12,637
- How long have you two been married?
- Five years.

221
00:16:14,115 --> 00:16:17,319
Second time around. That explains it.

222
00:16:17,798 --> 00:16:22,091
It's nice to meet you. I
hope to see you both tomorrow.

223
00:16:22,834 --> 00:16:24,817
A pleasure.

224
00:16:30,305 --> 00:16:33,982
<i>Mrs. Draper, Mrs. Barrett
is here at my desk.</i>

225
00:16:35,772 --> 00:16:38,514
No. Of course. Send her in.

226
00:16:41,555 --> 00:16:44,222
Mrs. Barrett, to what
do I owe the pleasure?

227
00:16:44,257 --> 00:16:46,890
- May I take your coat?
- No, thank you.

228
00:16:49,403 --> 00:16:51,781
I'm not sure how they do it
in show business, but around

229
00:16:51,782 --> 00:16:54,159
he we have this nifty gadget
called an appointment book.

230
00:16:54,194 --> 00:16:55,713
I was in the neighborhood.

231
00:16:55,748 --> 00:16:58,624
What did Jimmy do now,
ask Eleanor Roosevelt

232
00:16:58,625 --> 00:17:01,500
how fast her husband ran
the hundred-yard dash?

233
00:17:02,554 --> 00:17:05,537
- How are you?
- Busy.

234
00:17:06,815 --> 00:17:09,211
I have an idea for a television show.

235
00:17:09,246 --> 00:17:10,947
Congratulations.

236
00:17:10,982 --> 00:17:13,297
Is it too early to have a drink?

237
00:17:13,332 --> 00:17:16,264
- Let me call for some ice.
- No need.

238
00:17:16,299 --> 00:17:19,594
How do I make this
happen? Where do I go?

239
00:17:19,629 --> 00:17:21,124
What is it?

240
00:17:21,159 --> 00:17:25,107
Everyone loves Candid Camera,right?
Hidden camera situations.

241
00:17:25,142 --> 00:17:30,080
Only Jimmy's the host, and
he's Jimmy, you know? Not nice.

242
00:17:30,982 --> 00:17:35,603
It's derivative, with a twist.
